    "description": "Hill reps build strength and power that translates directly to EcoTrail's terrain. Outdoors: find a steady hill with a moderate gradient. Drive your knees, lean slightly forward from the ankles, and keep a strong arm swing. Jog back down easy — the downhill IS the recovery. Treadmill: set a fixed incline (5-6%) for the entire session. Hard reps at 10-12 km/h, recovery at 4-5 km/h walk.\n\nWarmup\n- 10m 66-78% LTHR (111-132 bpm)\n\nMain set 6x\n- Uphill 2m 99-112% LTHR (167-188 bpm)\n- Downhill 3m 66-78% LTHR (111-132 bpm)\n\nCooldown\n- 5m 66-78% LTHR (111-132 bpm)",
